geneVariantDescriptions.description: ALK G1202R lies within the protein kinase domain of the Alk protein (UniProt.org). G1202R has been demonstrated to confer drug resistance in the context of ALK fusions (PMID: 22277784, PMID: 24736079), but has not been biochemically characterized and therefore, its effect on Alk protein function is unknown (PubMed, Sep 2019).

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, Repotrectinib (TPX-0005) inhibited ALK G1202R and suppressed tumor growth in cell line xenograft models with ALK G1202R (AACR, Cancer Res: April 2016; Volume 57, Abstract #2132).
